# UART Test Program for RV32I
# 1. Write 'a' (0x61) to 0x4000 (UART data address)
# 2. Write 0x2 to 0x4004 (write enable bit)  
# 3. Loop: read 0x4004, if bit 0 is 1 then continue loop, else stop

# Assembly instructions and their hex encoding:

# li t0, 0x61        # Load 'a' character into t0
